  "prompt": "\"CAS PRES CHQ\" what does this SBI statement message mean?",
  "response": "The message \"CAS PRES CHQ\" on an SBI (State Bank of India) statement typically refers to a \"Cash Payment for a Cheque.\" This indicates that a cheque was presented for encashment, and cash was disbursed for it. Essentially, it means a cheque that you or someone else issued was cleared, and cash was withdrawn from your account. If you have further specific questions about a particular transaction, it's always best to reach out directly to SBI customer service for clarification.",
